description:
Why we do what we do
â€œAccording to Forbes 85% of business communication is
repetitive, time consuming, costly but imperative for
enterprise success. Therefore we have developed an AI
Process Automation for Enterprise Business Communication
(support, supply chain, HR, finance,...) via Slack/Teams/E-Mail/Voice/...
that automates Communication and Databases for enterprise
customers/employees to save time, cost and boost
customer/employee satisfaction.â€

Why we are different
State of the Art for automation companies was the static anthology approach which needs human interaction to grow with companies over time for helping them to automate business processes. We go one step further. We dynamically automate up to 80% of business processes in real-time. Our patented genetic coding system enables continuous learning with constant improvement in quality and accuracy of automation.

APA Technology
We have developed a patented novel NLU architecture built upon an in- depth analysis of text structure using recent breakthrough in computer linguistics, and a set of self-organized ML approaches (supervised/unsupervised, reinforcement, etc). To get best of both NLP and ML we implemented automatic source code generation, based on rethought genetic algorithm.

Mission & Vision
We have been working on AI products since 2015 to help people to focus on the important things in life. So we decided to help enterprises managing successfully their transition to the â€œEmpathy Economyâ€ via our AI Process Automation.

We believe that in the years to come 85% of repetitive actions in enterprises will be handled by machines and that we are one of the leading companies that are shaping this near future.

People & Culture
We are driven by technology but we understand that great technology is only built by great teams of people so we believe in

- People & Culture
- Communication
- Execution


    W Jefferson Blvd,  Los Angeles, California  US
tagLine: AI Process Automation for Enterprise Business Communication

description:
Founded in 2013, React Mobile is a global leader in providing panic button solutions to help organizations protect their employees. Our best in class hospitality safety platform helps hotels keep their employees safe and allows management to deploy resources to the exact location of an emergency within seconds of an alert, getting help to where they need it fast. In an emergency quick response times are essential.

Hoteliers realize that housekeeping staff that needs to enter into guest rooms alone can sometimes find themselves in vulnerable situations. Having help available at the press of a button is not only reassuring to staff it could potentially prevent serious emergencies or additional liability from occurring in the first place.

The React Mobile platform utilizes both GPS geolocation and blue tooth beacon technology to provide unparalleled accuracy to locate an employee in distress. Their technology works both on and off the hotel property and is equally applicable to a large distributed resort-style property as it is to a multi-story hotel tower. Inside of a building, the React Platform uses blue tooth beacon technology to pinpoint the exact location of a distress call. Outside of the building the system reverts to GPS coordinates and can follow an incident in progress in real-time relaying up to the second location information. 

The React Mobile solution is also able to leverage existing technologies that a hotel may already have in place to provide an elegant and robust safety platform at the lowest cost possible. For example, many of their customers use some form of housekeeping software like Amadeus HotSoS. The React Mobile software can pull room location information in from integrations with these types of software and further reduce the cost of deploying a robust employee safety solution.
    720 Seneca St,  Seattle, Washington  US
tagLine: React Mobile is the most robust and reliable staff safety platform available today.
